revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== {{suffix|en|xylem|like}} ===Adjective=== {{en-adj}} # Resembling or characteristic of a [[xylem]]. #* '''1963''', Pennsylvania Academy of Science, ''Proceedings of the Pennsylvania Academy of Science'' #*: In the medulla of callus formed in this fashion, a number of lignified cells occurred resembling the '''xylemlike''' cells often found in callus tissue.
